The macros for chapter "Refining disordered structures" 
are organised into subdirctories.

The line underneath the short description of the refinement topic gives
the program to use (discus/diffev) and the main macro that should be 
used to start the refinement.

For each DIFFEV refinement, the corresponding subdirectories
contain 3 KUPLOT macros that display information about the current refinement:

kpara.mac    Development of the R-value/ a parameter versus the generation
kpar_par.mac R-value versus parameter value for a given generation or
             Correlation between two parameter values for a given generation
ksingle.mac  Displays the current calculated data in comparision to the 
             experimental data.

================================================================================

RMC          Reverse Monte Carlo Refinement of short range order 
             in CuAu
             discus: rmc1.mac

EXAMPLO0     Short range ordered structure
             diffev: ref.ex0.diffev.mac

ZNSE.POWDER  Refinement of the ZnSe nanoparticle based on X-ray powder data
             diffev: diffev.mac

ZNSE.PDF     Refinement of the ZnSe nanoparticle based on X-ray PDF data
             diffev: diffev.mac

